t your mind smiles; when you cry, it means that your mind cries!\n\n- Mehmet\n|\nBaseball happens to be a game of cumulative tension but football, basketball and hockey are played with hand grenades and machine guns.\n\n- John\n|\nPursuit of passion, dream of dreamers!\n\n- Lailah Gifty Akita, Think Great: Be Great!\n|\nIf someone hurts you, he is hurting himself. He may not be able to escape that hurt in his lifetime.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nUltimately, my love saved me, for my love gave me strength. At night, when sleep was sunwilling to rescue me, I gritted my teeth and devoured my fondest memories.\n\n- John Shors, Beneath a Marble Sky\n|\nMany men, One CryOne Woman, a Pleasant Pride.\n\n- Goitsemang\n|\nPorsche is a driver's car - a performance car. That was funny - here's this awesome car, but it's got no cup holders.\n\n- Jason\n|\nHe started to estrange her... And they became strangers Who knew each other's heart, So broken as they drifted apart.\n\n- Ana Claudia Antunes, Pierrot & Columbine\n|\nI have better understanding how difficult and complex life can be, fortunately I know when not to take things so seriously and just enjoy every moment\n\n- Shellie\n|\nWhen you stop blaming others for where you are in life, that is when you can start to manifest your dream life!\n\n- Stephen\n|\nUnshed tears leave a deposit on your heart. Eventually they form a crust around it and paralyze it, the way mineral deposits paralyze a washing machine.\n\n- Susanna Tamaro, Follow Your Heart\n|\nBroken things can be made whole again. Perhaps not as they were before, but maybe stronger this time.\n\n- Carrie Ryan, The Dark and Hollow Places\n|\nThe pain of dying will surely be nothing, for the pain of love is so much stronger and agonizing.\n\n- Marilena\n|\n-Bumblebee bat, how do you see at night?-I make a squeaky sound that bounces back from whatever it hits. I see by hearing.\n\n- Darrin Lunde, Hello, Bumblebee Bat\n|\nFollow your heart, not the latest headlines.\n\n- T.F. Hodge, From Within I Rise: Spiritual Triumph Over Death and Conscious Encounters with 'The Divine Presence'\n|\nBear in mind, children, that they listen to you because you are kids—not because you are right. That's how our Father listens to us.\n\n- Rich\n|\nVirtue is harder to be got than knowledge of the world; and, if lost in a young man, is seldom recovered.\n\n- John\n|\nI don’t want my pain blanked out, he thought to himself; I need to keep my pain. It is a part of who I am, every bit as integral as the joy I’ve felt.\n\n- Mark Samuels, Glyphotech and Other Macabre Processes\n|\nYou have told me, O God, to believe in hell. But you have forbidden me to think...of any man as damned\n\n- Pierre\n|\nOh human creatures, born to soar aloft,Why fall ye thus before a little wind?\n\n- Dante Alighieri, The Divine Comedy\n|\nI think fear is normal, Cade. Just don't let it win.\n\n- Lisa\n|\nWhen God gives you a dream, He will grant you the grace to fulfil it.\n\n- Lailah Gifty Akita, Think Great: Be Great!\n|\nAs a sea is full of drops of liquid, I was but one in the ocean of WarMany are swept ruthlessly into the battering, bashing waves, and only few survive to swim to shore\n\n- Jade\n|\nWhat does the world teach you? It teaches you (to do) egoism. Then, from that egoism, arise many many phases!\n\n- Dada\n|\nPeople think that to love is simple, but that to find the right object to love - or to be loved by - is difficult.\n\n- Erich Fromm, The Art of Loving\n|\nYour pretty empire took so long to build, now, with a snap of history's fingers, down it goes.\n\n- Alan Moore, V for Vendetta\n|\nTo be forced to endure something because you have no money to counter it ; this fact is totally unfair and I can't, personally, tolerate it.\n\n- Laure\n|\nCourage to dare,Strength to act.\n\n- Lailah Gifty Akita, Think Great: Be Great!\n|\nI am not to be underestimated. Overestimated, maybe, but underestimated? No.\n\n- Saumya Sharman, The Ultimate Journey\n|\nBut she didn’t want to rest! – Her blood ran through her more slowly, its pace domesticated, like a beast that had trained its steps to fit in its cage.\n\n- Clarice Lispector, Near to the Wild Heart\n|\nThoughts eat me creepy words crush my head.. I hear them talk,they scream and howl for each other.. Weeping souls longing trapped in a cage full time.\n\n- Unknown\n|\nAt this moment, I saw more clearly than ever the brutalizing effects of slavery upon the slave and slaveholder.\n\n- Frederick\n|\nTo ensure health in mind, body and spirit; increase giving and receiving love.\n\n- Renae A. Sauter, An Empowered Life: Mind/Body/Spirit Empowerment\n|\nI recall the Scriptures into my mind, therefore, I have hope.\n\n- Lailah Gifty Akita, Think Great: Be Great!\n|\nYou can be anywhere you want in the world, meet different people and learn more than a hundred things in a matter of minutes… all you have to do is READ!\n\n- C.M.\n|\nAlthough you hadn't asked why, it had less to do with you not noticing than with you not wanting to hear the answer.\n\n- Jodi Picoult, Handle with Care\n|\nNo matter what your struggles are, everyone has their own level of greatness.\n\n- Angela\n|\nHoga Gothyelk no longer felt anger, not truly -- only varieties of sorrow.\n\n- R. Scott Bakker, The Darkness That Comes Before\n|\nMaster the chaos within yourself and I promise you, you will gain the strength to withstand any storm.\n\n- Nikki\n|\nHere lies the body of Colonel Cornell’s. The rest of the fellow, I fancy, in hell is.\n\n- Mark Hodder, The Strange Affair of Spring Heeled Jack\n|\nCome, let us speak with our bodies.Teach me how to please you.I am here to learn.Let us not waste this time.It is the hour of union.ComeAnd after you do,Come again.\n\n- Kamand\n|\nA lion is not afraid of walking alone, even if the whole jungle is pursuing it.\n\n- Matshona\n|\nThe more I read the Quran, the clearer I see the hidden wickedness lurking in the shadows of my soul.\n\n- Moosa\n|\nWe’re so rarely called on to be Christians, but when we are, we’ve got men like Atticus to go for us.\n\n- Harper Lee, To Kill a Mockingbird\n|\nLeadership: In love with the team, not the spotlights.\n\n- Alin\n|\nDon't let yourself be amazed by the imagination of a writer and his words, writers are almost all the time in a love-hate relationship with words.\n\n- Nema\n|\nThe thing about our choices is that after we have made them, they turn around and make us.\n\n- Abhysheq Shukla, KISS Life  'Life is what you make it'\n|\nReal inspiration are not people, but their stories.\n\n- Amit Kalantri, One Bucket of Tears\n|\nit is always yesterday, tomorrow, and 3 years ago today. It is always your birthday. It is always the future, the present, and the past. It is always eternity that will last.\n\n- Antonia\n|\nAlone in the dark, a great light illuminated my path.\n\n- Lailah Gifty Akita, Pearls of  Wisdom: Great  mind\n|\nNobody can give you freedom, nobody can give you equality or justice. If you are a man, you take it.\n\n- Malcolm\n|\nI'm a chess piece. A pawn,' she said. 'I can be sacrificed, but I cannot be captured. To be captured would be the end of the game.\n\n- Paolo Bacigalupi, Ship Breaker\n|\nWhen pretending starts, growth stops\n\n- Renae A. Sauter, An Empowered Life: Mind/Body/Spirit Empowerment\n|\nIf you will not die for us, you cannot ask us to die for you.\n\n- Jacqueline Carey, Kushiel's Dart\n|\nThose who find courage to pursue their dreams, manifest gladness of their souls.\n\n- Lailah Gifty Akita, Pearls of  Wisdom: Great  mind\n|\nMay we continue to encourage one another, so that we will increase in strength and in wisdom.\n\n- Lailah Gifty Akita, Pearls of  Wisdom: Great  mind\n|\nGretchen Lowell was beautiful in a very grown-up way, in a sophisticated, confident way. It was more than beauty; it was the power of beauty. She radiated it.\n\n- Chelsea Cain, Heartsick\n|\nWhat is in great demand, but scarce, is expensive, but even when wisdom is not in demand it is priceless.\n\n- Matshona\n|\nYou live and die in the batting of my eyes. You cast a wavering shadow over the snow for a day. I cast my shadow over empires across eons.' - Orm Hinn Langi the Dragon\n\n- Lou Anders, Frostborn\n|\nAfter dissolution of fears, your mind and emotions act in harmony to help you to make you a joyous soul. You don’t need to do extra efforts to get what you desire.\n\n- Hina Hashmi, Your Life A Practical Guide to Happiness Peace and Fulfilment\n|\nMen of honor, men of God in a healthy society, stand in defense of justice\n\n- Sunday\n|\nYour life is the only journey, you travel unaided.\n\n- Lailah Gifty Akita, Think Great: Be Great!\n|\nAs thou know not what is the way of the spirit, nor how the bones do grow in the womb of her that is with child: even so thou know not the works of what makes all.\n\n- Compton\n|\nYou may forget the toys you buy and break, but you'll always remember the experiences and memories you create.\n\n- Richie\n|\nBy reading, we will know the minds of great soul.\n\n- Lailah Gifty Akita, Think Great: Be Great!\n|\nWhen a Promise of Leadership is neglected or unfulfilled, trust is broken, engagement erodes, and performance suffers.\n\n- William A.  Adams, Mastering Leadership: An Integrated Framework for Breakthrough Performance and Extraordinary Business Results\n|\nThe gray paint peels off the wall in odd and beautiful patterns, each cracked polygon of paint a snowflake of decay.\n\n- John Green, Paper Towns\n|\nNever feel that you are alone, as someone is always be your side.\n\n- Mitch\n|\nWe too can repair our cracks with goldAnd glow again.Crazed by life,More beautiful than ever before.\n\n- Scott\n|\nSome people think the stars must look closer from up here. They don't. When you're up here, you realize how distant they really are—how impossible to reach.\n\n- Ally Condie, Reached\n|\nGeorge looked at her for a long moment. Finally he replied, 'And why do you find it so hard to think someone might like you and want to do things for you?\n\n- Tamora Pierce, Alanna: The First Adventure\n|\nIf one attains only the faith in the Self, he will not experience fear anywhere at all, fear will go away.\n\n- Dada\n|\nDon't you know there ain't no devil, it's just god when he's drunk.\n\n- Tom\n|\nAll women speak two languages: the language of men and the language of silent suffering.  Some women speak a third, the language of queens.\n\n- Mohja Kahf, E-mails from Scheherazad\n|\nStagnation is death. With love, accept and welcome changes.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nIf there are occasions when my grape turned into a raisin and my joy bell lost its resonance, please forgive me. Charge it to my head and not to my heart.\n\n- Jesse\n|\nWhen knowledge is limited - it leads to folly... When knowledge exceeds a certain limit, it leads to exploitation.\n\n- Abu\n|\nShe can feel his blood, just beneath his skin; when he breathes, the air fills with smoke. He's like a dragon, ancient and fearless.\n\n- Alice Hoffman, Here on Earth\n|\nI go on the presumption that everyone's full of shit until proven otherwise, and this usually serves me in good stead.\n\n- Dennis Lehane, A Drink Before the War\n|\nTime flies over us, but leaves its shadow behind.\n\n- Nathaniel\n|\nRelationships based on dishonesty, lies,Secrets and cheats R not only predictedto fail but also a waste of precious timeand energie! U can’t fool yourself 4ever!\n\n- Lily Amis, Angel of Love  Lily: Zak, My Sweet Inspiration\n|\nMay power of the Holy Spirit, renew your thoughts and attitudes.\n\n- Lailah Gifty Akita, Think Great: Be Great!\n|\nStay stupid. Follow your unconventional, crazy heart.\n\n- Steven Pressfield, Do the Work\n|\nSuffering is just about the easiest of all human activities; being happy is just about the hardest. And happiness requires, not surrender to guilt, but emancipation from guilt.\n\n- Nathaniel\n|\nI used to say why save money if I'll die tomorrow, I haven’t died yet and I have nothing to survive on\n\n- Bangambiki Habyarimana, The Great Pearl of Wisdom\n|\nYour soul is oftentimes a battlefield, upon your reason and your judgment wage war against your passion and your appetite.\n\n- Kahlil Gibran, The Prophet"